headline: 1 Software Stock to Keep an Eye On and 2 We Find Risky
summary: From commerce to culture, software is digitizing every aspect of our lives. The undeniable tailwinds fueling SaaS companies have led to lofty valuation multiples historically, but rich prices also make re-ratings harder and place a ceiling on returns - over the past six months, the industry’s 19.9% gain has lagged the S&P 500 by 6 percentage points.
